My project uses an Arduino UNO with 11 LEDs connected to digital pins 2 through 12. 
Each LED has a resistor to protect it from too much current, 
and all the negative legs are connected to the GND of the Arduino through the breadboard.

The way it works is simple. The LEDs light up one at a time from left to right, 
starting from pin 2 all the way to pin 12, 
with each LED staying on for half a second before the next one turns on. 
Once it reaches the last LED on the right, 
the sequence reverses and the LEDs sweep back from right to left, 
from pin 12 back to pin 2. This back and forth motion repeats continuously in a loop, 
creating a smooth sweeping animation across all 11 LEDs.
